      • acknowledge

        public void acknowledge(String path,
                        boolean cleanup)
        Acknowledges this flow for the given path. The flow part representing this path is set to status FlowStatus.CLEAN. If cleanup is set to true then the packet field containing the initial message is set to null but only if the number of expected acknowledgements has been reached. This saves disk storage but prevents the flow from being replayed. Clears the flow part message text.
        Parameters:
        path - a flow path.
        cleanup - true to enable cleanup of the initial message if the expected acknowledgement count has been reached.
        See Also:
        acknowledge(String, boolean, String), setFlowMessageText(String)

      • acknowledge

        public void acknowledge(String path,
                        boolean cleanup,
                        String partMessageText)
        Acknowledges this flow for the given path. The flow part representing this path is set to status FlowStatus.CLEAN. If cleanup is set to true then the packet field containing the initial message is set to null but only if the number of expected acknowledgements has been reached. This saves disk storage but prevents the flow from being replayed. Saves the partTextMessage in the FlowPart.
        Parameters:
        path - a flow path.
        cleanup - true to enable cleanup of the initial message if the expected acknowledgement count has been reached.
        partMessageText - a the part text message for the FlowPart with path path to be saved.
        See Also:
        setFlowMessageText(String)

      • invalidate

        public void invalidate(String path)
        Invalidates this flow for the given path. The flow part representing this path is set to status FlowStatus.ERROR. Clears the flowPart message text.
        Parameters:
        path - a flow path.

      • invalidate

        public void invalidate(String path,
                       String partTextMessage)
        Invalidates this flow for the given path. The flow part representing this path is set to status FlowStatus.ERROR.
        Parameters:
        path - a flow path.
        partTextMessage - a the part text message of the FlowPart with path path to be saved.

      • update

        protected FlowPart update(String path,
                          FlowStatus status)
        Updates this flow for the given path. The flow part representing this path and status is created or updated by incrementing the contribution count and setting the contribution time to the current time.
        Parameters:
        path - flow path.
        status - flow status to set.
        Returns:
        the updated FlowPart
        See Also:
        FlowPart

      • filter

        public boolean filter(String path)
        Determines whether to filter this flow at a given path. If the flow should be filtered this method returns true and the filter count is incremented by 1. The filter time is updated to the current time.
        Parameters:
        path - a flow path.
        Returns:
        a hint to filter implementations to filter out this flow at the given path.

      • isReplayable

        public boolean isReplayable()
        Returns true if this flow can be replayed. A flow can only be replayed if the initial message (packet) is stored i.e. the packet must not be null.
        Returns:
        true if the flow can be replayed.

      • prepareReplay

        public byte[] prepareReplay()
        Prepares this flow for a replay by updating the replay time and replay count. Clears the message text of the flow parts.
        Returns:
        the message data (packet) used for replay.
